JOHANNESBURG – Former Orlando Pirates player, Bheka Phakathi has died, the club said on Sunday. “Orlando Pirates Football Club is saddened to learn of the passing away of former player Bheka Phakathi, “ the club said on its website. According to Kickoff.com, Phakathi died in a car accident on Sunday morning while he was on his way to training. Condolences to Phakathi Family
